Fine Needle Aspiration (FNA) market is segmented based on the type, sample type, and end-user. The market is divided into fine needle aspiration biopsy and fine needle aspiration cytology based on type. Fine needle aspiration biopsy involves the removal of cells for examination, while cytology involves the evaluation of individual cells. In terms of sample type, the market includes blood, bone marrow, pleural fluid, and other sample types. Blood samples are commonly used for diagnostic purposes. The end-user segment comprises hospitals, diagnostic centers, research institutes, and other healthcare facilities utilizing FNA procedures for diagnosis and analysis purposes.

